HEADWORD: Erinite
<hw>Er"i*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
hydrous arseniate of copper, of an emerald-green color; -- so called
from <etsep>Erin</etsep>, or Ireland, where it occurs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

